-- South African Tiger Tracked Down by a Dog; Returned to Owner, Star Reports
-- Paul Richardson
-- 2010-07-29T05:34:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/south-african-tiger-tracked-down-by-dog-returned-to-owner-star-reports.html

          
          
             Panjo, the 17-month-old Bengal tiger
that went missing in South Africa after jumping off a sports
utility vehicle, has been found after being tracked down by a
dog,  The Star  reported,  
 A Weimaraner hunting dog found the tiger hiding in the
bushes near a main road southwest of Groblersdal, about 170
kilometers (67 miles) northeast of Johannesburg, the Star said.  
 Searchers had failed to locate the animal using pickup
trucks, a helicopter, loudhailers and thermal imaging equipment,
the Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  
